The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Junior?s death numbs Goa

OUR CORRESPONDENT

Panaji: The whole of Goa struggled to come to grips with Cristiano de Lima Junior?s death even as his lifeless body of was flown in from Bangalore. 

Dempo?s Brazilian striker collapsed on the Kanteerava Stadium pitch Sunday afternoon following a collision with Mohun Bagan goalkeeper Subrata Pal seconds after he had scored his second goal of the Federation Cup final. He was rushed to hospital but didn?t regain consciousness. 

Our Staff Reporter in Calcutta adds: The East Bengal flag flew at half mast on Monday as the club where Junior made his India debut last season paid its homage to the prolific striker. 

East Bengal club also announced an ex-gratia contribution of Rs 1 lakh for Junior?s family. It follows equal amounts announced by Karnataka chief minister N. Dharam Singh and the Karnataka State Football Association. 

